We know it’s risky out here for black organizers, but this story had us clutching our pearls. Founder of @untilfreedom #TamikaMallory details her experience getting followed by drones for five blocks on her way home after a protest for Breonna Taylor in Louisville, Kentucky. She says the local police department denied their involvement, and she’s unsure of who the culprit is ‘til this day. 👀 Watch the full interview on YouTube- link in bio. 

Be sure to check out Tamika's New Book #StateOfEmergency available everywhere now! She’s also on a virutal book tour, visit www.TamikaDMallory.com to reserve your ticket.

node.text:
TSR STAFF: Jade Ashley @Jade_Ashley94
_____________________________________ 
Back in May #NaomiOsaka made headlines after she decided to make her mental health a priority and issued a warning that she would not be doing press while competing at the French Open. That ultimately led to her withdrawing from the tournament after the first round when she was fined for sticking to her promise. She would later withdraw from other tournaments as she placed her mental health first while preparing for the Olympics. 
_____________________________________
On Monday, Naomi was announced as one of the three cover stars for Sports Illustrated's latest swimsuit issue. While many people showed Naomi love for her cover, there were some who criticized her for appearing on the cover, as well as other covers but making the decision to not participate in press conferences following her matches. 
_____________________________________
One person, in particular, was #MegynKelly, who retweeted a tweet from Clay Travis who spoke about all of Naomi's recent endeavors, and Megyn added, "Let’s not forget the cover of (& interview in) Vogue Japan and Time Mag!" Naomi took a moment to gather Megyn and said in a now-deleted tweet, "Seeing as you’re a journalist I would’ve assumed you would take the time to research what the—read more at TheShadeRoom.com (📸: @gettyimages)
